Vice President Mike Pence visited Vandenberg Air Force Base in California and delivered a speech expressing gratitude to the men and women serving in the Armed Forces. He thanked the military families for their sacrifices and extended greetings from President Donald Trump. Pence highlighted the historical significance of Vandenberg Air Force Base in the space industry and praised their recent achievements, including successfully intercepting a test intercontinental ballistic missile. He emphasized the importance of the public and private sectors working together to advance American leadership in space. Pence also discussed the need to address emerging threats to space security and announced plans to establish the United States Space Force. He concluded his speech by expressing confidence in the dedication and professionalism of the servicemen and women at Vandenberg Air Force Base.